	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="csC1E9DC0"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION 1</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">(By Senators Smith (Mr. President), Morris, Phillips, Martin, Grady, Deeds, Woodrum, M. Maynard, Hamilton, Taylor, Rose, and Helton)</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Reported January 28, 2026, from the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure]</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs89687900"><a name="_Hlk219364726"><span class="csEF05ACC">Requesting the Division of Highways to name certain bridges and roads.</span></a></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><a name="_Hlk219124794"><span class="csEF05ACC">Whereas, The Division of Highways is requested to name the following transportation infrastructure:</span></a></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 50-037/13-001.96 (50A250), (38.18271, -82.40177) locally known as Peter Cave Bridge, carrying CR 037/13 over East Fork Twelvepole Creek in Wayne County, the &quot;Donald and Hercie Maynard Memorial Bridge&quot;; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 42-037/00-000.77&nbsp;(42A085), (38.76146, -79.92758) locally known as Valley Bend Truss, carrying CR 037 over Tygart Valley River in Randolph County, the &quot;U.S. Army SSgt. Gail Mason Kerns Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 21-1/25-0.01 (21A227), (39.047420, -80.465940) locally known as Weston Plate Girder, carrying CR 001/25 over West Fork River in Lewis County, the &quot;U.S. Army SGM Joe H. Pringle Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 41-041/00-001.83 (41A338), (37.79519, -81.17316) locally known as Cranberry Creek Bridge, carrying WV 041 over Cranberry Creek in Raleigh County, the &quot;U.S. Army SPC 5 James &ldquo;Russell&rdquo; Neely Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 32-023/00-001.18 (32A035), (37.52956, -80.77013) locally known as Indian Creek Bridge, carrying CR 023 over Indian Creek in Monroe County, the &quot;U.S. Army Pvt. James Robert &quot;Bob&quot; Long Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 23-010/28-000.01 (23A190), (37.72987, -81.86311) locally known as Huff Junction Box Beam, carrying CR 010/28 over Huff Creek in Logan County the &quot;U.S. Army SSG Barney Warren Frazier, Sr. Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">A section of US 119 from Mile Point 7.45 (37.7604533</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="csEF05ACC">, -82.3117637) in Mingo County&nbsp;to Mile Point 24.02 (38.5414478, -81.3495006) in Roane County, the &quot;Purple Heart Trail&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">A portion of County Route 3/2, also named Moses Fork Road, from its intersection at Old County Road (37.872177, -82.174614) to its intersection at East Fork of Twelvepole Road (37.872016, -82.151667) in Mingo County, the &quot;Donald Tackett, Jr. Memorial Road&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 30-065/83-000.05 &nbsp;(30A283), (37.79354, -82.34353) locally known as Tug Valley High School Bridge, carrying CR 065/83 over Pigeon Creek in Mingo County, the &quot;Wilburn Thomas &quot;Hawkie&quot; Preece Jr. Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 06-025/00-004.54 &nbsp;(06A057), (38.38821, -82.11303) locally known as Zoar Church Bridge, carrying CR 025 over Mud River in Cabell County, the &quot;U.S. Army CPL Winfred Glen Dillon Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 39-072/00-001.85 (39A236), (39.28332, -79.73050) locally known as Etam Bridge, carrying WV 072 over Buffalo Creek in Preston County as the &quot;Clinton &quot;Randy&quot; Dean 101st Airborne Vietnam Veterans Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 16-007/00-015.36 (16A019), (38.97829, -78.97689) locally known as Harness Ford Bridge, carrying CR 007 over S.FK.S.BR.POT.RIV. in Hardy County, the &quot;U.S. Army SSG Orval Riggleman Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 12-050/00-006.13 &nbsp;(12A132), (39.2698, -79.26228) locally known as Stony River Bridge, carrying US 050 over Stony River in Grant County, the &quot;U.S. Army LTC James Douglas Moreland Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">A section of WV Route 20 in Lerona/Pipestem, WV from (37.504620, -80.971419) to (37.544255, - 80.970262), the &quot;Early Pioneer John W. &ldquo;Buttermilk&rdquo; Neely Memorial Road&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">A section of US 119 from Mile Point 27.5 (37.861672, -82.047612) to Mile Point 33.5 (37.934514, -82.012865), the &quot;Sergeant Cory S. Maynard Memorial Road&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">A section of Route 20 in Webster Springs from (38.478838, -80.416653) to (38.426010, -80.453451) the &quot;U.S. Army CPT Ernest &quot;Jack&quot; Morton, Jr. Memorial Road&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 04-079/00-067.01 (NB &amp; SB) (04A119, 04A120), (38.70312, -80.66296) locally known as Flatwoods Interchange North &amp; South, carrying IS 079 over CR 19/22 in Braxton County, the &quot;John K. &amp; Virginia E. Skidmore Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number 01-021/00-000.56 (01A065), (39.09071, -80.00151) locally known as Laurel Run W-Beam, carrying CR 021 over Laurel Run in Barbour County, the &quot;Mt. Liberty Veterans Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number: 50-041/00-002.29 (50A097), (37.96566, -82.34511) locally known as Cabwaylingo Box Beam, carrying CR 041 over West Fork Twelvepole Creek in Wayne County, the &quot;Richard P. Maynard Memorial Bridge&quot;;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Bridge number: 04-013/02-003.21 (04A015), (38.65994, -80.75910) locally known as Heck&rsquo;s Bridge, carrying CR 013/02 over Elk River in Braxton County, the &quot;WV Supreme Court Justice Tim Armstead Memorial Bridge&quot;; therefore, be it</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Resolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="csEF05ACC">That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to name transportation infrastructure specified in this resolution; and, be it</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Further Resolved</span><span class="csEF05ACC">, That the Clerk of the Senate is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the Commissioner of the Division of Highways.</span></p>


